  "texts": [
    "For instance, the AI Act [37] impose obligations around algorithmic transparency and provisions (especially Articles 13 and 14) against manipulative AI systems that intersect with the DSA's focus on mitigating algorithmically amplified disinformation [62,78].",
    "To delineate these relations, we report here the main regulations likely to impact the DSA in terms of platforms and data governance.• The General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) [45],in force since 2018, establishes horizontal rules governing the processing and free movement of personal data in the EU.",
    "Its key principles include lawfulness, fairness and transparency; purpose limitation; data minimization; accuracy; storage limitation; and accountability.",
    "The regulation applies broadly to organizations processing EU residents' personal data.",
    "In terms of connections, the GDPR and DSA potentially align on transparency duties around data processing activities."
  ],
